  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table bordercolor=\"#000080\">\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Goats and\n        ...</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>From <em>Othello</em>, William\n        Shakespeare (4.1.300). These words mark the point at\n        which Iago has convinced Othello that his wife has been\n        unfaithful to him and he decides to return to Venice,\n        where he will eventually kill Desdemona and himself.\n        (Also hints forward to Shylock, who uses the goats in the\n        Bible to justify usury.)</font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Othello and \"Burbank\"</td>\n<td><a href=\"Carnaval_EG.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><font>Rhetoric and Drama in Burbank</font></td>\n<td><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Shylock and usury</td>\n<td><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Structural analysis</td>\n<td><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Goats and ... From Othello , William Shakespeare (4.1.300). These words mark the point at which Iago has convinced Othello that his wife has been unfaithful to him and he decides to return to Venice, where he will eventually kill Desdemona and himself. (Also hints forward to Shylock, who uses the goats in the Bible to justify usury.) reference topics Othello and \"Burbank\" Rhetoric and Drama in Burbank Shylock and usury Structural analysis back to \"Burbank\"",
